{
  "texts": [
    "On MMLU clinical topics, Med-PaLM 2 significantly improves over previously reported results in Med-PaLM 1 and exceeds previous state-of-the-art performance on three out six topics, with GPT-4-base reporting better numbers in the other three.",
    "We note that the test set for each of these topics is small, as reported in Extended Data Table 1.",
    "We see a drop in performance between GPT-4-base and the aligned (production) GPT-4 model on these multiple-choice benchmarks (Table 1).",
    "Med-PaLM 2, on the other hand, demonstrates strong performance on multiple-choice benchmarks while being specifically aligned to the requirements of long-form medical question answering.",
    "While multiple-choice benchmarks are a useful measure of the knowledge encoded in these models, we believe human evaluations of model answers along clinically relevant axes are necessary to assess their utility in real-world clinical applications."
  ]
}